some kids call it the grocerystore 
school and some parents call it a godsend its a babysitting 
service at the supermarket that lets parents in peace and leaves 
more room in the cart for groceries 
its definitely helpful especially when a mother has only two 
hands and two children and is trying to grocery shop said 
35yearold karen redfearn who drives 17 miles from herrin to shop 
at the country fair store in carbondale 
its terrific she said 
located at the front of the country fair store the babysitting 
center has a color tv a video cassette recorder a 55gallon 
aquarium two bulletin boards five bean bags five plastic trucks 
and cars and stuffed animals 
but if junior still gets bored theres a 60piece set of wooden 
building blocks a xylophone an etchasketch a toy telephone and 
a toy cash register safety scissors glue and paint brushes 
crayons markers and paper complete the picture 
the 18by16foot area is a separate room from the store it has 
brown carpeted floors and its walls are decorated with drawings by 
the children 
big windows allow parents to check in on their youngsters while 
they shop 
my biggest problem is trying to get the kids to leave on 
time said sandy overstreet 23 coordinator of the carbondale 
