and lodged under a pier in san francisco bay on saturday officials 
said 
mary jane schramm a spokeswoman with the california marine 
mammal center in sausalito said it wasnt immediately known if the 
whale was dead when it washed under pier 70 or if it died after 
getting under the structure 
the whale had deep slash marks on its head and some of them 
involved the animals blow hole which allows it to inhale and 
exhale said schramm 
schramm feared the marks could have been caused by a ships 
propeller but she did not rule out the possibility they were made 
by a veterinarian who examined the dead whale after it was found 
he could not be reached for comment 
whales often hug the california coastline while migrating 
between arctic waters and the warmer baja california waters from 
january through may schramm said 
authorities were relieved to learn that the dead whale was not 
the juvenile whale that was spotted several times in recent weeks 
frolicking around the bay she said 
