records show he told the succeeding psychiatrists in a letter 
incidentally i do hope that you are charging her a full fee 
for your housecalls and visits she can well afford it 
during the years mrs lederer was a patient of pollock 
she established a trust fund that has paid pollock 50000 a 
year since 1976 and will continue paying him through 1993 she 
established a second trust that has paid pollocks family 30000 a 
year since 1978 court records arent clear when the second trust 
expires 
from 1969 until her death mrs lederer donated 601330 to the 
chicago institute for psychoanalysis of that money 60233 went 
to a depression research fund controlled by pollock 
in 1980 she created the anne p lederer research institute 
pollock worked for a short time as a paid consultant to the 
institute but said in his affidavit that there is no secret 
agreement for him to participate in its future operations he 
also denied receiving any benefit from mrs lederers will 
