several thousand dollars to two grandchildren and the rest of her 
money estimated at 5 million to the lederer research 
institute she also named pollock schanfield and continental 
illinois national bank amp trust co as coexecutors of her estate 
tepper said mrs lederers son was worth about 2 million before 
her death and that when she died he inherited about 6 million from 
a trust established by her father ej pollock vice president and 
comptroller of sears roebuck amp co in the 1930s the two pollock 
families are not related 
mrs lederer referred to her sons wealth to explain in her last 
will why she was leaving most of her money to my foundation 
