<TEXT>
city officials have installed 
about 450 concrete trash cans downtown in a bid to limit damage and 
injuries from frequent bomb attacks 
the bins have been designed to cause the least possible damage 
in the event of an explosion a city official told the sunday 
times newspaper 
they are as near bombproof as its humanly possible to make 
them he said of the thick concrete bins 
two years ago the city removed 1300 metal trash cans and 2500 
polemounted bins and replaced them with mesh baskets in hopes that 
making the contents of bins more visible would deter bombers 
new bins have been placed in the middle of city blocks instead 
of on corners to make it more difficult for someone to 
surreptitiously plant bombs 
there have been more than 70 bombings in south africa since the 
government imposed a nationwide emergency in 1986 and many have 
been in the johannesburg area 
police have blamed virtually all of the attacks on the outlawed 
african national congress the main black group fighting to 
overthrow the government 
